2 Cleaning the Data

2.1 Telehealth Dataset

Code 
# Telehealth Data Cleaning

# Load the data
Telehealth <- read.csv("Telehealth Dataset/Medicare Telehealth Trends.csv", header = TRUE)
# Remove all rows with any missing (NA) values
Telehealth <- na.omit(Telehealth)
Code 
# Telehealth rename variables
Telehealth <- Telehealth %>% rename(Quarter = quarter)
Telehealth <- Telehealth %>% rename(State = Bene_Geo_Desc)
Telehealth <- Telehealth %>% rename(EnrollmentStatus = Bene_Mdcd_Mdcr_Enrl_Stus)
Telehealth <- Telehealth %>% rename(Race = Bene_Race_Desc)
Telehealth <- Telehealth %>% rename(Sex = Bene_Sex_Desc)
Telehealth <- Telehealth %>% rename(MedicareAccessForInsured = Bene_Mdcr_Entlmt_Stus)
Telehealth <- Telehealth %>% rename(Age = Bene_Age_Desc)
Telehealth <- Telehealth %>% rename(RuralUrban = Bene_RUCA_Desc)
Telehealth <- Telehealth %>% rename(EligibleServicesCount = Total_Bene_TH_Elig)
Telehealth <- Telehealth %>% rename(EnrollmentPartB = Total_PartB_Enrl)
Telehealth <- Telehealth %>% rename(TelehealthVisits = Total_Bene_Telehealth)
Telehealth <- Telehealth %>% rename(PercentTelehealthPartB = Pct_Telehealth)

2.2 Population Dataset

Code 
# Load the data
Population <- read.csv("Population Dataset/Annual Estimates of the Resident Population for the United States.csv", header = TRUE, sep = ",")

# Remove leading dots from state names in both datasets
Population$State <- gsub("^\\.+", "", Population$State)

# Standardize 'District of Columbia' in both datasets to ensure a match
Population$State <- gsub("District of Columbia", "District of Columbia", Population$State)
Telehealth$State <- gsub("District Of Columbia", "District of Columbia", Telehealth$State)

Population <- Population %>%
  rename(
    BasePopulation2020 = Base.Population.April.2020,
    `2020POP` = X2020,
    `2021POP` = X2021,
    `2022POP` = X2022,
    `2023POP` = X2023,
    `2024POP` = X2024
  )

# Reshape Population: Convert wide format (multiple years as columns) to long format (single 'Year' and 'POP' columns)
Population_long <- Population %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("20"), # Select columns with years
               names_to = "Year",
               values_to = "POP") %>%
  mutate(Year = as.numeric(gsub("POP", "", Year))) # Convert 'Year' to numeric

# Merge Telehealth and reshaped Population data on State and Year
TelehealthandPopulation <- merge(Telehealth, Population_long, by = c("State", "Year"), all = TRUE)

# Remove all rows with any missing (NA) values - includes States labeled National, Virgin Islands, Midwest, West, South, Northeast, Territories
TelehealthandPopulation <- na.omit(TelehealthandPopulation)

# Removing Columns that are Not Needed 
TelehealthandPopulation <- dplyr::select(TelehealthandPopulation, -BasePopulation2020)

Code

  t() %>%
  as.data.frame(stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

# Store original column names as a new column

  mutate(Original_Column_Names = rownames(Vehicle_transposed2023))

# Set first row as column names

# Remove the first row, keeping the new column names
Vehicle_transposed2023 <- Vehicle_transposed2023[-1, ]

Merging all the Vehicle transposed data

Code 
# Remove 2024 from TelehealthandPopulation before merging
TelehealthandPopulation <- TelehealthandPopulation %>%
  filter(Year != 2024)
Code 
# Create a list of the vehicle datasets
vehicle_data <- list(
  "2020" = Vehicle_transposed2020,
  "2021" = Vehicle_transposed2021,
  "2022" = Vehicle_transposed2022,
  "2023" = Vehicle_transposed2023
)

# Convert each yearâs vehicle data into a long format and combine
Vehicle_long <- bind_rows(
  lapply(names(vehicle_data), function(year) {
    vehicle_data[[year]] %>%
      mutate(Year = as.numeric(year)) # Add the year as a column
  })
)

# Merge the reshaped Vehicle dataset with TelehealthandPopulation on State and Year
TelehealthandPopulation_Vehicle <- merge(TelehealthandPopulation, Vehicle_long, by = c("State", "Year"), all = TRUE)

  as.numeric(cleaned_x)

# Create a list of the vehicle datasets
Poverty_data <- list(
  "2020" = Poverty_transposed2020,
  "2021" = Poverty_transposed2021,
  "2022" = Poverty_transposed2022,
  "2023" = Poverty_transposed2023
)

# Convert each yearâs vehicle data into a long format and combine
Poverty_long <- bind_rows(
  lapply(names(Poverty_data), function(year) {
    Poverty_data[[year]] %>%
      mutate(Year = as.numeric(year)) # Add the year as a column
  })
)
Code 
Poverty_long <- Poverty_long %>%
  mutate(
    Populationforwhompovertystatusisdetermined = str_remove(Populationforwhompovertystatusisdetermined, "%"),
    Populationforwhompovertystatusisdetermined = as.numeric(Populationforwhompovertystatusisdetermined) / 100
  )

Poverty_long <- Poverty_long %>%
  rename(PercentPoverty = Populationforwhompovertystatusisdetermined)
Code 
# Merge the reshaped Internet dataset with TelehealthandPopulation_Vehicle on State and Year
TelehealthandPopulation_VehicleInternetHospitalPoverty_GDPUNRATE_Transit <- merge(TelehealthandPopulation_VehicleInternetHospital_GDPUNRATE_Transit, Poverty_long, by = c("State", "Year"), all = TRUE)

## Population Dataset

```{r}
# Load the data
Population <- read.csv("Population Dataset/Annual Estimates of the Resident Population for the United States.csv", header = TRUE, sep = ",")

# Remove leading dots from state names in both datasets
Population$State <- gsub("^\\.+", "", Population$State)

# Standardize 'District of Columbia' in both datasets to ensure a match
Population$State <- gsub("District of Columbia", "District of Columbia", Population$State)
Telehealth$State <- gsub("District Of Columbia", "District of Columbia", Telehealth$State)

Population <- Population %>%
  rename(
    BasePopulation2020 = Base.Population.April.2020,
    `2020POP` = X2020,
    `2021POP` = X2021,
    `2022POP` = X2022,
    `2023POP` = X2023,
    `2024POP` = X2024
  )

# Reshape Population: Convert wide format (multiple years as columns) to long format (single 'Year' and 'POP' columns)
Population_long <- Population %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("20"), # Select columns with years
               names_to = "Year",
               values_to = "POP") %>%
  mutate(Year = as.numeric(gsub("POP", "", Year))) # Convert 'Year' to numeric

# Merge Telehealth and reshaped Population data on State and Year
TelehealthandPopulation <- merge(Telehealth, Population_long, by = c("State", "Year"), all = TRUE)

# Remove all rows with any missing (NA) values - includes States labeled National, Virgin Islands, Midwest, West, South, Northeast, Territories
TelehealthandPopulation <- na.omit(TelehealthandPopulation)

# Removing Columns that are Not Needed 
TelehealthandPopulation <- dplyr::select(TelehealthandPopulation, -BasePopulation2020)

```

```{r}
                        "FourVehicleAvailable", "FiveOrMoreVehicleAvailable",

                        "OneRentVehicleAvailable", "TwoRentVehicleAvailable", 
                        "ThreeRentVehicleAvailable", "FourRentVehicleAvailable", 
                        "FiveOrMoreRentVehicleAvailable", "TotalWithInternet", 
                        "WithInternet", "DialUpNoInternetSubs", 
                        "BroadBandAnyType", "CellularData", 
                        "CellularDataAndAnotherType", "CableFiberOrDSL", 
                        "CableFiberOrDSLOnly", "SatelliteInternet", 
                        "SatelliteInternetOnly", "OtherServiceOnly", 
                        "InternetAccessNoSubscription", "NoInternet")

# Apply gsub to clean each column before conversion

  # Remove non-numeric characters
  cleaned_x <- gsub("[^0-9.-]", "", x)
  # Convert to numeric
  as.numeric(cleaned_x)
```

```{r}
# Transpose using pivot_longer and pivot_wider
Poverty_transposed2023 <- Poverty2023 %>%
  t() %>%
  as.data.frame(stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

# Store original column names as a new column
Poverty_transposed2023 <- Poverty_transposed2023 %>%
  mutate(Original_Column_Names = rownames(Poverty_transposed2023))

# Set first row as column names
colnames(Poverty_transposed2023) <- Poverty_transposed2023[1, ]

# Remove the first row, keeping the new column names
Poverty_transposed2023 <- Poverty_transposed2023[-1, ] 

# Remove all non-letter characters from column names
colnames(Poverty_transposed2023) <- gsub("[^A-Za-z]", "", colnames(Poverty_transposed2023))

colnames(Poverty_transposed2023) <- make.unique(colnames(Poverty_transposed2023))

Poverty_transposed2023 <- Poverty_transposed2023 %>% rename(State = LabelGrouping)

# Remove "Margin.of.Error"
Poverty_transposed2023 <- Poverty_transposed2023[!grepl("Margin.of.Error", rownames(Poverty_transposed2023)), ]

# Remove "..Total..Estimate"
Poverty_transposed2023 <- Poverty_transposed2023[!grepl("..Total..Estimate", rownames(Poverty_transposed2023)), ]

# Remove "..Below.poverty.level..Estimate"
Poverty_transposed2023 <- Poverty_transposed2023[!grepl("..Below.poverty.level..Estimate", rownames(Poverty_transposed2023)), ]

# Rename row names by removing "..Percent.below.poverty.level..Estimate"
rownames(Poverty_transposed2023) <- gsub("\\.\\.Percent\\.below\\.poverty\\.level\\.\\.Estimate", "", rownames(Poverty_transposed2023))

Poverty_transposed2023 <- Poverty_transposed2023 %>%
  mutate(State = str_replace(State, "\\.\\.Percent\\.below\\.poverty\\.level\\.\\.Estimate$", ""))

Poverty_transposed2023 <- Poverty_transposed2023[, c("State", "Populationforwhompovertystatusisdetermined")]

```

```{r}
Poverty_data <- list(

  "2021" = Poverty_transposed2021,
  "2022" = Poverty_transposed2022,
  "2023" = Poverty_transposed2023
)

# Convert each yearâs vehicle data into a long format and combine
Poverty_long <- bind_rows(
  lapply(names(Poverty_data), function(year) {
    Poverty_data[[year]] %>%
      mutate(Year = as.numeric(year)) # Add the year as a column
  })
)
```

```{r}
  mutate(

  )

  rename(PercentPoverty = Populationforwhompovertystatusisdetermined)
```

```{r}
  "American Indian/Alaska Native" = "#A6CEE3",  # light blue

  "Black/African American" = "#A8D08D", #green

)

# Create bar plot for Telehealth Visits by Race
TelehealthandPopulation_VehicleInternetHospital_GDPUNRATE_Transit %>%
  filter(Race != "All") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Race, y = TelehealthVisitsPerCapita, fill = Race)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  labs(title = " ",
       x = "Race Category",
       y = "Sum of Number of Telehealth Visits (Per Capita)") +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::comma) +  # Format y-axis with full numbers and commas
  scale_fill_manual(values = race_colors) +  # Apply color palette
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, size = 9),  # Increased font size
```

# Fixed Effect

## Multivariable

```{r}
model1 <- lm(TelehealthVisitsPerCapita ~ TotalOwnedPerCapita + TransitSpendingScore + WithInternetPerCapita + CableFiberOrDSLPerCapita + SatelliteInternetOnlyPerCapita + HospitalCountPerCapita + NoofPhysiciansPerCapita + GDP_trillions + UNRATE_prop,TelehealthandPopulation_VehicleInternetHospital_GDPUNRATE_Transit) # without State/Year fixed effects

model2 <- lm(TelehealthVisitsPerCapita ~ TotalOwnedPerCapita + TransitSpendingScore + WithInternetPerCapita + CableFiberOrDSLPerCapita + SatelliteInternetOnlyPerCapita + HospitalCountPerCapita + NoofPhysiciansPerCapita + GDP_trillions + UNRATE_prop + State, TelehealthandPopulation_VehicleInternetHospital_GDPUNRATE_Transit) # with State fixed effects

model3 <- lm(TelehealthVisitsPerCapita ~ TotalOwnedPerCapita + TransitSpendingScore + WithInternetPerCapita + CableFiberOrDSLPerCapita + SatelliteInternetOnlyPerCapita + HospitalCountPerCapita + NoofPhysiciansPerCapita + GDP_trillions + UNRATE_prop + State + Year, TelehealthandPopulation_VehicleInternetHospital_GDPUNRATE_Transit) # with State and Year fixed effects

regz <- list(`No Fixed Effect` = model1,
             `State Fixed Effect` = model2,
             `State and Year Fixed Effect` = model3)

coefz <- c("TotalOwnedPerCapita" = "Vehicles Owned",
           "TransitSpendingScore" = "Transit Spending Per Capita",
           "WithInternetPerCapita" = "With Internet",
           "CableFiberOrDSLPerCapita" = "Cable Fiber Or DSL",
           "SatelliteInternetOnlyPerCapita" = "Satellite Internet Only",
           "HospitalCountPerCapita" = "Hospitals Count",
           "NoofPhysiciansPerCapita" = "Number of Physicians",
           "GDP_trillions" = "GDP",
           "UNRATE_prop" = "Unemployment Rate")

gofz <- c("nobs", "r.squared")

rowz <- as.data.frame(matrix(c('State Fixed Effects', "No", "Yes", "Yes",
                               "Year Fixed Effects", "No", "No", "Yes"),
                             byrow = TRUE, nrow = 2)) # 2 rows
attr(rowz, 'position') <- c(24, 25)

modelsummary(regz,
             estimate = "{estimate}{stars}",
             gof_map = gofz,
             add_rows = rowz,
             coef_map = coefz)
```

## VIF Calculation

```{r}
# Load necessary package
library(car)  
library(knitr)

# Fit the model (excluding fixed effects for accurate VIF calculation)
vif_model <- lm(
  TelehealthVisitsPerCapita ~ TotalOwnedPerCapita + TransitSpendingScore + WithInternetPerCapita + HospitalCountPerCapita + NoofPhysiciansPerCapita + PercentPoverty + GDP_trillions + UNRATE_prop, data = TelehealthandPopulation_VehicleInternetHospitalPoverty_GDPUNRATE_Transit
)

# Calculate VIF
vif_values <- vif(vif_model)

# Format VIF output into a data frame
vif_df <- data.frame(
  Variable = names(vif_values),
  VIF = round(vif_values, 2)  # Round to 2 decimal places
) %>%
  arrange(desc(VIF))  # Sort in descending order

# Remove redundant variable names in the Variable column
vif_df$Variable <- gsub(".*", "", vif_df$Variable)  # Clean up redundant text

# Print formatted VIF values using kable for a neat table
kable(vif_df, col.names = c("Variable", "VIF"), caption = " ", format = "markdown", digits = 2)

```
